To find the measure of angle \( \angle AFD \) in quadrilateral \(ABCD\), we start by analyzing the given information and the trisection of angles \( \angle BAD \) and \( \angle CDA \).

First, we know the measures of angles \( \angle ABC \) and \( \angle BCD \):
\[
\angle ABC = 110^\circ \quad \text{and} \quad \angle BCD = 100^\circ.
